text.section:
The Council on Postsecondary Education shall develop and implement a system of accountability for the postsecondary education institutions that measures:
Educational quality and educational outcomes;
Student progress in the postsecondary system;
Research and service activities;
Use of resources;
Other performance or outcomes that support the achievement of the strategic agenda, including involvement in quality enhancement of elementary and secondary education; and
Other indicators as deemed appropriate by the Council on Postsecondary Education.
